# Write and maintain Cursor rules

Rules live in `.cursor/rules/ai-rules/<subfolder>/<name>.mdc` (Markdown + YAML frontmatter). Treat them as short internal playbooks, not essays.

## Filenames

- **kebab-case**, **verb-first** when natural (e.g. `write-clean-code.mdc`).
- Always `.mdc`. Name describes one topic; the `description` adds nuance.

## Frontmatter

| Field | Type | Purpose |
|-------|------|---------|
| `description` | string | One line shown in the rule picker; specific enough to choose this rule. |
| `globs` | string | Optional. Path glob; rule is considered when matching files are in context. |
| `alwaysApply` | boolean | If `true`, the rule is in every chat for this project—use sparingly. |

**Scope**

- `alwaysApply: true` — project-wide norms (style, security, how we ship). Few rules; each must earn its token cost.
- `alwaysApply: false` + `globs` — stack- or area-specific rules.
- `alwaysApply: false` and **no** `globs` — only for meta rules toggled by mode commands.

## Body

- One `#` title.
- **Bullets > prose**—scannable constraints.
- Short ❌/✅ snippets only when easy to misread.
- One concern per file; **aim under ~50 lines**. Split when longer.

## Quality bar

- Actionable bullets, not slogans.
- `description` is unique and actionable—no `Rules` / `Misc` / `Important`.
- Examples copy-paste realistic; pull from this repo when possible.
- No duplicate guidance—link or consolidate.
- No secrets or environment values (rules are versioned).

## Maintenance

- Update examples when APIs or folder layout change.
- Fix `mdc:` links when rules are renamed or split.
- Mark outdated guidance clearly; remove rules that no longer apply with a one-line migration hint.
- External links: prefer stable URLs; verify they resolve.

## Before merging a new rule

- [ ] Path is `.cursor/rules/ai-rules/<subfolder>/<kebab-case>.mdc`.
- [ ] Frontmatter parses (no dangling `globs:` without a value).
- [ ] `description` is unique and actionable.
- [ ] Scope is intentional (`alwaysApply` vs `globs` not fighting).
- [ ] No duplicate guidance.
